column5: Took this creature off a 44" Muskie...I have removed many over the years but they are still just as ugly as the first time.
a whole lot of nasty there
Those little critters have rights to you know...
You have to be careful with those toothy buggers, I hear the slime off them will rust your pliers in mere seconds.
What did you use for that Matt?  Fish Crisp or Darryl Chronzy's batter....  Tom.
Where's the picture of your musky? Haha just kidding dude. Ugly bugger for sure!  Cheers, Ryan
Since you asked!    Good fight casting the cowgirl on a weedbed at dusk
Yep that's a UGLY bugger for sure. I here some salt and pepper little oil and cast iron and you have a great snack there.  Nice Ski Matt
Nice Ski, and yep, nasty little buggers ain't they, yuck!  Joey
That's actually kind of neat.  I'm guessing that's a silver lamprey (Ichthyomyzon unicuspis) as opposed to the dreaded (and hated) sea lamprey (Petromyzon marinus).
